author: news@mpnews.net (Staff)
title: IW volleyball wins second straight conference game
text:
IW volleyball wins second straight conference game Oct 14, 2015 
The Iowa Wesleyan womenâ€™s volleyball team hosted Eureka College for a conference match Tuesday at 7 p.m. Iowa Wesleyan picked up their second straight conference win after defeating the Red Devils in three straight sets. The Tigers won 25-14, 25-18, and 25-19. 
Iowa Wesleyan won the first set in a decisive manor. The Tigers had 15 kills and just three attack errors compared to seven kills and five errors. The Red Devils did not make it as easy in the second set, forcing the Tigers into seven attack errors. Iowa Wesleyan once again out hit their opponent, 12 to nine in kills. 
The final set of the night saw the scoring go back and forth for a bit. Eureka took an early lead but the Tigers fought back to tie it up and eventually would take the lead for good. Both teams had double digit kills in the set, but the Red Devils committed 10 attack errors to help the Tigers get the victory. 
Cassandra Schwamborn had a team high 9 kills in the match and Sydney Ellsworth finished with 7 kills. Cierra Howard led the team defensively with 17 digs for the night. Maggie Earney recorded 36 assists in the match against the Red Devils. 
Iowa Wesleyan will return to action Friday, October 16th. They will travel to Greenville, Illinois to take on Greenville College at 7 p.m.
